es.csic.iiia.nsm.norm.refinement.iron

Class PotentialGeneralisation

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.csic.iiia.nsm.norm.refinement.iron.PotentialGeneralisation

  • public class PotentialGeneralisation
extends java.lang.Object
    An potential generalisation of IRON is a generalisation that the NSM may potentially perform for a particular group of norms. Each potential generalisation contains:
    1. a potential parent norm that may be created if a set of child norms fulfil certain conditions to be generalised to the parent; and
    2. a List of children, namely a list of child norms that must exist and perform well to be generalised to a parent norm.
    Author:
    "Javier Morales (jmorales@iiia.csic.es)"
    See Also:
    GeneralisationReasoner, GeneralisationTrees
